  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Forecast based Anticipatory Early Action to Support Disaster Preparedness for the Flood Affected Vulnerable Households</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving transfer of unconditional cash to flood-prone families in Rangpur (Gaibandha, Kurigram), Rajshahi (Bogura, Sirajganj) and Mymensingh (Jamalpur). In collaboration with the Bangladesh Red Crescent, WFP distributes $53 to each household, to help them meet their essential food and non-food needs in the immediately prior to and immediately following the flooding. The project provides life-saving assistance to 309,500 people, including nearly 93,500 women, 69,000 boys and 65,000 girls.</narrative>
  </description>
